	   <tr><td colspan=2>The fact of the matter is that they roughly come out to be the same, but it depends on your preference.<br>Having one 2HS weapon will take twice as long, but deal twice as much damage.<br>Having two 1HS where dmg/dly come out to to be the same will take only half as long to hit, but will only do half of the damage.<br>Having one 2HS weapon will help you when you are in need of a big hit, and having two 1HS will help you when you are looking for a chain of constant hits.<br><br><br>Dalastdon Corlione<br>E'ci Barbarian Warrior<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
