<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100871337736899></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100871337736899><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=1&mid=100871337736899>RE: 2x1 or 1 x2</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=1&mid=100871337736899#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93579><span id=Scholar>Yosa</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>48 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 18th 5:09 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.42]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Weather you should use two one hand weapons or one two hand weapon Depends on your lvl, what weapons you have to choose from, and what kind of Mob you are fighting.  <br>First you should keep as many weapons skill lvl maxed as possible.  <br>You can compare one and two hand weapons as follows. <br>Until your skill approches 200, your off hand weapon will hit noticable less than your primary.<br>So calculate the damage rate of your primary, and off hand weapons.  Multiply the damage rate of your off hand weapon by 0.67 and add the two together and then calculate the damage rate of you two hand weapon.  Which ever is highest will do the most damage.<br>This compairason becomse more difficult, as you have to start taking into account Str bonus for the primary hand and weapon damage bonus.  <br>Also pre lvl 20 there is a damage cap you have to consider if you are twinked, or using a high damage two hand weapon.  <br>Most often it is best to use two one hand weapons, however I used a 30/40 2hb with very good results.  <br>Furthermore some mobs have damage shiled so you take damage every time you hit them.  I have seen some warrior damage shiled them self nearly to death buy using fast low damage weapons againest such mobes.  Another case is higher lvl mobs that use melee abilities just like high lvl warrior, one of which is the mob hits you back everytime you hit it, here again a fast low damage weapon will be the death of you.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
