<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100834926393795></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100834926393795><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=1&mid=100834926393795>Hast, Combat System and Weapons</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=1&mid=100834926393795#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93579><span id=Scholar>Yosa</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>48 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Dec 14th 12:01 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Haste:<br>Haste items do not stack.  You get the effect of one haste item.  However you can stack haste effects, by having the spell cast on you, while using a haste item.  Or by having an item that procs haste, and a haste item.<br><br>Combat System:<br>In EQ combat is based on weapon delay.  When you are using one weapon it works like this<br>Weapon cycles (delay clocks out)<br>Roll is made to see if you hit or miss.<br>Weapon cycles<br>and so on.<br>Using two weapons is as follows<br>Fastest weapon cycles<br>if the fastes weapon is held in the off hand<br>Roll is made to see if you duel weild<br>If roll is made, Roll to see if you hit or miss<br>Slower weapon cycles<br>If this weapon is in the primary slot Roll is made to see if you hit or miss.  <br>So each weapon functions indapendantly, but the off hand weapon has to make one more roll, in order to attack.  <br><br>Choosing a Weapon:<br>At lower lvl there are two things to consider when chossing a weapon.  One is how much damage the weapon will do in a standard round (grin) and the seconed is how fast your skill will go up using the weapon.  <br>In EQ you have to preform a task x times in order for your skill to go up.  Because of this fact your 1hs skill will rase faster if you use a Lanseax 6/23 than if you used Bargynn's digger <br>8/30.  Both weapon will do about the same damage per standard round, but you would swing the lan more often and thus your skill will go up faster.  <br><br>This board usese the Raito to compair weapons.  I like to use damage per standerd round (DPSR).  Or how much damage each weapon would do in the same amount of time.  One way to calculate this is to devide the damage by the delay and then times by 200. This will tell you the avg amount of damage done by the weapon if the standard round had a delay of 100.  Which give you a better idea if the weapon is enough better than your existing one to justify the time or pp to obtain.  <br><br>Most of the time you should use your best weapon in your primary slot (lowest ratio or highest DPSR) <br><br>When your duel weild skill is low it is advantagous to use a fast weapon in the off hand to rase your skill. <br><br>You do not need to do the math to check this out.  Just put diffrent types of weapons in the primary and off hand.  With the faster weapon in the off hand, at lower lvl you will only very rarely see it hit first, however with a skill of 200 the faster weapon hits first 90% of the time if it is held in the off hand.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

