	   <tr><td colspan=2>At level 16, as a &quot;good&quot; Warrior, the best place to go is High Hold Pass. It is very easy to start at 16 with the Gnolls on the Kithicor ent. to High Hold. You should not have a problem finding a group there, and the Gnolls will take you to level 18. You will also have a chance for the PGT, both a decent weapon, and good sale item at about 75pp or so, depending on your server. You then can move to the other side of the Pass, the East Karana ent. side, and work on Orcs to level 20. At that point, you will be ready to move to High Hold Keep, where you can level all the way to 30 very quickly...I went from 16-32 in one week RL play time using this strategy. Some advantages to this zone are the facts that the Keep guards are very close to your fighting areas, and any mobs or trains they can't handle, Ran Flamespinner in the Library can, as he hits for 300 or so, and can save you EVERY time. Small Bronze Armor drops here, which your Dwarf can use...most players are willing to let you contribute 6pp to the group split for each piece of armor...rather cheap for the AC. There is a Bank in the zone also, so you can bank...fight...get armor...and have fun all in a very small zone area. Some people will tell you LOIO is a better place to go at 19 or so...but having played both zones with different characters, I give the nod to High Hold. Get on EQ Atlas and find the zone connections and locations, and also read up on Allakhazam's zone sections for these areas. It is best to go into an area fully prepared for what you will find there...good luck young Warrior... :)<br>&nbsp;<br>Tenuvan - 36 WE Druid<br>Klatuu  - 42 HE Warrior<br>Keanor  - 20 DE Necro<br>Drinal server</td></tr>
